
[1]pegmatite

   PEG'MATITE, n. Primitive granitic rock, composed essentially of
   lamellar feldspar and quartz; frequently with a mixture of mica. In it
   are found kaolin, tin tourmaline, beryl, aqua marina, tantale, scheelin
   and other valuable minerals.
